## Location of Plesk Resources

Plesk has some default to do operations like add/remove ip address, backup management, migration manager, database, SSL manager etc..

- You can get the resource details from Plesk >> Click on Tools & Settings from Left side menu.
- Under Resources you can get the plesk resources


## IP Address Management

- Go to Plesk >> From left side menu click **Tools & Settings**. 
- Under Resources Click on **IP Address**. From here you can see the current IP address of your server and option to add/remove IPs. To modify existing IP settings, then click on the IP address.

```diagram

```

### Add New IP Address

- Click on Add IP address Link. 
- In the next window select your interface, write your IP address, select the ip address type and select ssl certificate if you have

```diagram

```

- Then click on OK button.

### Remove Existing IP Address

- Select the IP Address from the list and then click on **Remove** button


```diagram

```

### Modify IP Address Settings

- Click on the IP address from the IP list.
- In the next window you can modify SSL certificate/default website of that specific IPs.



## SSL Certificates

Before installing SSL make sure you have created CSR and purchases License for that..

This tutorial describe how to create SSL signing request and install SSL certificate on a domain from Plesk 10

1. Generate CSR and Purchase SSL certificate
1. Click here for SSL order Procedure
1. SSL certificates are installed on fully qualified domain names (FQDN). That means if you purchase it for domain.com, it can not be installed on www.domain.com or subdomain.domain.com
1. Domain must be on a dedicated IP address. Check this article (need to link article to here)

**Generating CSR**

- Login to the Plesk Control Panel as an administrator.
- To manage your certificates on PLESK go to: Tools & Utilities > SSL Certificates (in the Resources group).
- To create a new certificate request click Add SSL Certificate and specify the certificate properties:

    - Certificate name. This will help you identify this certificate in the repository.
   - Fill in the form as explained here under:
   - **Encryption level**: Choose the encryption level of your SSL certificate (more than 2048-bit).
   - **Country**:: provide the contry in which your company is based.
   - **State**: in France indicate the name of the department where your company headquarters are based (not the number).
  - **City**: indicate the city where your company headquarters are based.
  - **Organisation**: indicate the corporate name of your company (no trade name or acronym), in uppercase preferably.
  - **Organisational unit / Department / Branch**: If needed, indicate the department that manage the server.
  - **Domain name**: Indicate here your SSL server name, such as "secure.company.com", "www.my-domain.com" or "www.product.com". 
  - **E-mail**: E-mail address of the personn in charge of the certificates mamagement in your company

- Finally, click "Request" NOT ""Self-signed". You will then be redirected to your certificates management page. The private key and certificate signing request have been generated and stored in this repository.

**Installing SSL**

To install your newly purchased SSL certificate via Plesk, please follow the below instructions:

On your Parallels Plesk Panel.

1. Click on the **Tools & Settings** link on the left panel.
2. Click on the **SSL Certificates** icon.
3. Click on the **Certificate name** (which already created when creating CSR)
4. Scroll down and enter the **Certificate and CA certificate** in the provided boxes.
5. Click on the **Send Text** button.

**Check SSL support is enabled via Plesk**

To check that your SSL certificate is enabled in Plesk, please follow the below instructions:

On your Parallels Plesk Panel.

1. Click on the **Domains** link on the left panel.
2. Click on the **Control Panel** link next to the relevant domain name.
3. Click on the **Websites** and domains tab.
4. Scroll down and click on the relevant domain name.
6. Under the Security section, click on the tick box for **Enable SSL support**.
7. Scroll down and click on the **OK** button.

## How to Redirect httpsdocs to httpdocs - For SSL


> After installing SSL from plesk, the url https://www.domain.com showing 403 FORBIDDEN message
{.is-danger}


**Solution**

When you set up an SSL certificate on a domain set up through Plesk then automatically when viewing your website over this SSL cert (i.e. https://domain.com rather than http://domain.com) then the webserver will look for these files in the httpsdocs folder rather than the httpdocs folder for security.

If you have an SSL cert set up on one of your domains you might prefer to use the standard httpdocs folder when using the SSL cert rather than the httpsdocs folder.

This can be done on some of the newer versions of Plesk under:

- **Domains » domain name » Website Setup » Enable the “Use a single directory for housing SSL and non-SSL content”** option here.

As the above has only been available in new versions of plesk


## How to Choose Correct cert for a domain from a list

If Plesk shows several SSL certificate for particular domain , then we need to choose a correct one from that list.

Here the steps,

Go to **Plesk » Domains » Domain name » Webhosting settings**. Choose the correct certificate from drop down box and click “OK”.
